KEY POINTS:

вҖў Iterable вҶ’ Root interface for traversing collections.
вҖў Collection вҶ’ Root interface of List, Set, and Queue.
вҖў List вҶ’ Ordered collection, allows duplicates.
вҖў Set вҶ’ Unordered collection, no duplicates.
вҖў Queue вҶ’ Used for processing elements in FIFO/Priority order.
вҖў Map вҶ’ Stores key-value pairs (not part of Collection hierarchy).

COMMON IMPLEMENTATIONS:

вҖў ArrayList      вҶ’ Fast random access
вҖў LinkedList     вҶ’ Fast insertion/deletion
вҖў Vector         вҶ’ Synchronized dynamic array
вҖў Stack          вҶ’ LIFO data structure
вҖў HashSet        вҶ’ Unique unordered elements
вҖў LinkedHashSet  вҶ’ Maintains insertion order
вҖў TreeSet        вҶ’ Sorted set
вҖў PriorityQueue  вҶ’ Priority-based queue
вҖў ArrayDeque     вҶ’ Double-ended queue
вҖў HashMap        вҶ’ Key-value storage, fast lookup
вҖў LinkedHashMap  вҶ’ Maintains insertion order
вҖў TreeMap        вҶ’ Sorted key-value pairs
вҖў Hashtable      вҶ’ Thread-safe map
вҖў Properties     вҶ’ Used for configuration properties



